PROJECT.PROJECT_TITLE: Isotopic Ratio Outlier Analysis Global Metabolomics ofCaenorhabditis elegans
PROJECT.PROJECT_SUMMARY: We demonstrate the global metabolic analysis ofCaenorhabditis elegansstress using a mass-spectrometry-based technique called isotopic ratio outlier (IROA). In an IROA protocol, control and experimental samples are isotopically with 95 and 5%13C, and the two sample populations are mixed together for extraction, sample preparation, and LC-MS analysis.To illustrate the utility of for global metabolomics, we exposed wild-type (N2) worms to a heat shock (30 heat shock at 33 C), which causes significant, widespread changes in We collected and analyzed material from the exometabolome (all material that release in the supernatant) and the endometabolome (homogenized total extracts the worm bodies).

STUDY.STUDY_TITLE: Heatshock response of C. elegans using IROA (I)

COLLECTION.SAMPLE_TYPE: whole young adult C. elegans Heat shock | supernatant Heat shock | whole young C. elegans Control | supernatant Control
COLLECTION.VOLUMEORAMOUNT_COLLECTED: 225,000 worms | 10 mL worm water | 250,000 worms | 10 mL worm water

TREATMENT.TREATMENT_SUMMARY: Heat Shock: Two successive synchronous generations of wild-type C. elegans (N2) grown in S-complete buffer at 22C containing 5% 13C-labeled E. coli. Upon the young adult stage, the population was washed from E. coli using standard and was divided into four replicates. Each replicate was treated with a 30 min shock at 33 °C followed by incubation at 22C for 1.5 hours. Control: Two synchronous generations of wild-type C. elegans (N2) were grown in S-complete at 22C containing 95% 13C-labeled E. coli. Upon reaching the young adult stage, population was washed from E. coli using standard procedures.
TREATMENT.TREATMENT_DOSEDURATION: 30C for 30 minutes; 1.5 hours at 22 C before harvest | 22C for 30 minutes; 1.5 at 22 C before harvest

The FR resolution was set to 70?000 at m/z 200. The achieved was routinely less than 1.5 ppm, externally calibrated.

MS.MS_COMMENTS: Samples were analyzed using a mass range of m/z 70-800 in positive and negative mode, externally calibrated, using a Thermo Scientific Q-Exactive Orbitrap mass equipped with an Open Accela autosampler and an Accela 1250 pump (San Jose, The Q-Exactive was equipped with a heated electrospray ionization (HESI) which operated at a spray temperature of 500 °C, a spray voltage of 3 kV, and and auxiliary gas flow rates of 60 and 10 arbitrary units, respectively. were extracted from the ms data using proprietary MATLAB IROA scripts. Ratios each feature (heatshock/control) were calculated for each replicate. Ratios normalized by setting the median log-fold change for each sample to zero
